  "prompt": "How do I stop my Jamster subscription from charging me money?",
  "response": "To stop your Jamster subscription from charging you, you typically need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log into Your Account**: Go to the Jamster website and log into your account using your credentials.\n\n2. **Access Subscription Settings**: Find the section related to your subscriptions or account settings. This may be labeled as \"My Account,\" \"Subscriptions,\" or something similar.\n\n3. **Cancel the Subscription**: Look for an option to manage or cancel your subscriptions. Follow the prompts to cancel the Jamster subscription. \n\n4. **Confirmation**: Make sure to confirm the cancellation and check for any confirmation email or notification.\n\n5. **Contact Customer Support**: If you encounter difficulties, reach out to Jamster\u2019s customer support for assistance. They should be able to help you cancel the subscription.\n\n6. **Check Payment Method**: Depending on how you set up your subscription (credit card, mobile billing, etc.), you may also want to monitor your payment method to ensure no further charges occur.\n\nRemember to do this before your billing cycle ends to avoid any additional charges. If you still keep getting charged after cancellation, contact your payment provider for further assistance.",
